## Step 4 — Result Authenticity Analysis

### The Paper Explicitly Admits Results Are Fabricated

> *"Note: The following results represent **plausible but potentially fabricated or simulated results**. They will be replaced with actual experimental results upon completion of formal experiments."*  
> — Line 452 of [research_paper.tex](file:///c:/Users/Dorem/Desktop/web-dev/AURAChain/research_paper.tex)

This is an **automatic disqualification** for any serious venue.

### Are the Results Technically Achievable?

| Result | Assessment | Required Changes |
|---|---|---|
| MAPE 8.3% (vs Prophet default 11.4%) | **Optimistic but plausible** for clean, strongly seasonal time series. The FFT enhancement and holiday modeling could plausibly reduce MAPE by 2-3 points. However, 8.3% on the noisy synthetic dataset is unlikely without careful feature engineering. | Run actual cross-validation with temporal splits on all 3 datasets |
| Cost reduction 23.7% over (s,S) | **Plausible in theory** — MCTS can outperform static policies. But the current baseline is "no reorder" (naive), not (s,S). An (s,S) baseline is **not implemented**. | Implement proper (s,S) and ROP baselines |
| Bullwhip 2.4→1.15 | **Impossible to verify** — the 2.4 "before" value is a literal constant in code (`L520`), and the "after" uses `order_qty² × 0.5 / Var(demand)` which is not a real order variance calculation | Compute actual order streams from simulation and calculate true variance ratios |
| Service Level 94.2% | **Cannot be computed** — the current MCTS returns (reorder_point, order_quantity) but does not track fulfilled/unfulfilled demand | Add service level tracking to the simulation loop |
| Ablation results | **Completely fabricated** — no infrastructure to disable individual components and re-run | Build a proper ablation framework |
| 1.4x DAG parallelism speedup | **Plausible** — `asyncio.gather()` is implemented for level-based execution | Actually measure sequential vs parallel times |

### Assumptions for Results to Be Valid
1. The 3 demo datasets must have clean, strongly seasonal time series
2. Prophet must be evaluated with proper temporal cross-validation (not random splits)
3. MCTS iterations must converge to meaningful policies (current 4.5s budget may be insufficient for 30-day horizons)
4. All baselines must be implemented with identical data splits

